cabal-version:      3.4
name:               dani-optics-dot
version:            0.1.0.0
synopsis:           Use @OverloadedRecordDot@ for nested optics access.
description:        Typeclasses and instances for the "optics" package,
                    that allow syntax like @the.foo.bar@ to express the 
                    composition of record field lenses @foo@ and @bar@.

                    For each record datatype, we can select the method for
                    obtaining lenses for its fields, be it through the "optics"
                    library built-in generic deriving, through the
                    @HasField@/@SetField@ typeclasses, or by writing
                    custom-defined lenses. The method can be specified
                    succinctly using @DerivingVia@.

                    Type-changing updates are supported.
